---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Deck Facelift — New Boards, Railings & Fascia | Belvedere Decks"
  description="Deck facelift in Montgomery County, MD: new composite boards, new railings, and new fascia on your existing frame. $24,000–$35,000 typical — a new deck's look without the rebuild."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Deck Facelift · $24,000–$35,000 typical</p>
      <h1>Everything you see is new. Everything sound stays.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        The Facelift is the biggest transformation per dollar in deck building: new
        composite boards, new railings, and new fascia on your existing frame. From the
        yard, it's indistinguishable from a brand-new deck — because everything you can
        see and touch is.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why it's our signature project</h2>
      <p>
        Montgomery County is full of decks whose bones are good and whose surfaces are
        tired — original wood boards gone gray, wobbly railings, cracked fascia. A full
        rebuild throws away a perfectly serviceable frame and pays to rebuild it. A
        facelift puts the money where your eyes and hands actually go.
      </p>

      <h2>What's included</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Removal of existing boards, railings, posts, fascia, and trim</li>
        <li>Full inspection of the exposed substructure — joists, beam, ledger, posts</li>
        <li>Replacement of rotted or bowed joists (stated allowance in the contract; additional only by written change order)</li>
        <li>New blocking secured around the perimeter</li>
        <li>Protective joist tape on every joist and beam</li>
        <li>Premium TimberTech or Trex boards with hidden fasteners, with a picture-frame border face-fastened with color-matched plugs</li>
        <li>New code-compliant railing posts and premium railing — 36″ guard, ≤4″ baluster spacing</li>
        <li>New PVC fascia wrapping the deck edge</li>
        <li>Lighting and re-connection of fixtures where selected</li>
        <li>Haul-away of everything old</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="notice">
        A facelift typically requires no building permit since the framing stays. Where any
        structural work is needed, we confirm with Montgomery County first — that's in the
        contract, not a verbal promise.
      </div>

      <h2>The range, honestly</h2>
      <p>
        Typical ~400 sq ft facelifts run <strong>$24,000–$35,000</strong>. What moves it:
        railing selection, fascia and lattice, stairs, and lighting. Three configurations,
        one exact price, same visit.
      </p>
      <p><a class="btn primary" href="/contact">Get your facelift price</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
